        "Answer": "The Company was legally justified. Under the Labor Code, (in Article 82). 'field personnel are among those classes of workers who are not entitled to overtime pay, and the phrase 'field personnel' includes sales representatives who. like other field personnel, are non- agricultural employee who regularly perform their duties away from the principal place of business or branch office of the employer and whose actual hours of work in the field cannot be determined with reasonable certainty."
