        "Answer": "No. In GMA Network, Inc v. Pabriga, it was ruled that the repeated hiring of project employees to perform tasks which are necessary and desirable in the usual business or trade of the employer is sufficient evidence of the necessity, if not indispensability, of the workers’ service to the employer’s business."
