        "Question": "Tito Paciencioso is an employee of a foundry shop in Malabon, Metro Manila... he asked his employer to stop deducting from his salary his SSS monthly contribution, reasoning out that he is waiving his social security coverage. If you were Tito’s employer, would you grant his request? Why?",
        "Answer": "No. As Tito’s employer, I am bound by law to remit to SSS Tito’s monthly contribution. The compulsory coverage of employers and employees under the SSS law is actually a legal imposition on the employers and employees, designed to provide social security to workingmen. Membership in SSS is in compliance with a lawful exercise of the police power of the State, and may not be waived by agreement of any party."
