        "Question": "Which of the following is not considered an employer by the terms of the Social Security Act? (2012 Bar Question) a. A self employed person; b. The government and any of its political subdivisions, branches or instrumentalities, including corporations owned or controlled by the government; c. A natural persons, domestic or foreign, who carries on in undertaking or activity of any kind and uses the services of another person who is under his orders as regards the employment; d. A foreign corporation.",
