        "subject": "Labor Law",
        "No": 159,
        "Question": "Falcon Factory is engaged in the assembling of automotive components... hired fifty (50) persons (engineers, architects and construction workers) to renovate its building... The workers contend that they are casual employees who are not subject to compulsory coverage under the Social Security Law. Do you agree with their contention? Explain your answer fully. ",
        "Answer": "Yes. Under Section 8 (j) of RA 1161, as amended, employment of purely casual and not for the purpose of the occupation or business of the employer are excepted from compulsory coverage. The work to be performed by these fifty (50) people is not in connection with the purpose of the business of the factory. Hence, the employ of these fifty (50) persons is purely casual. They are, therefore, excepted from the compulsory coverage of the SSS law."
