        "Answer": "No right of self-organization for Legal Secretaries — Legal Secretaries fall under the category of confidential employees with no right to self-organization. Confidential employees are those who assist or act in a confidential capacity to persons who formulate, determine, and effectuate management policies in the field of labor-management relations."
