        "Answer": "A. YES. The Secretary of Labor and Employment has plenary power to assume jurisdiction under Article 263(g) of the Labor Code. When in his opinion, there exists a labor dispute causing or likely to cause a strike or lockout in an industry indispensable to the national interest, he may assume jurisdiction over the dispute or certify the same to the NLRC for compulsory arbitration. B. NO. The general rule is that the parties should revert to the status quo ante litem, which means the time before the compulsory arbitration was filed. In this case, the strike already started. Thus, the Secretary should have issued a return to work order."
